    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of June 5 article about soft money and the presidential campaign, which misstated a Federal Election Commission rule</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article on Monday about soft money and the presidential campaign misstated a Federal Election Commission requirement for reporting how the contributions are used in issue advertising. The national party committees must disclose all receipts and expenses arising from unrestricted soft money donations. Issue advertisements, which may be paid for in part with soft money, are not exempt from disclosure requirements.</p>
      </block>
